<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77fe4565-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–7"><num value="460mmm–7">§ 460mmm–7.</num><heading> Public access</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id77fe4566-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–7/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall continue to allow private landowners reasonable access to inholdings in the Conservation Area and Wilderness.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id77fe4567-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460mmm–7/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Glade Park</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall continue to allow public right of access, including commercial vehicles, to Glade Park, Colorado, in accordance with the decision in Board of County Commissioners of Mesa County v. Watt (634 F. Supp. 1265 (D.Colo.; <date date="1986-05-02">May 2, 1986</date>)).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id77fe4568-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/353/s9">Pub. L. 106–353, § 9</ref>, <date date="2000-10-24">Oct. 24, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1380">114 Stat. 1380</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
